         What is grid?
         
It is working in 2-D dimensional.
An intersection of vertical and horizontal lines is called grid.
It can worked bothnrows and column.
Terminology associated with grid
Rows
Column
Element 
Gap
Line
Grid container are made of grid item that are arraned in rows and column.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
          Difference between grif and flex
GRID
CSS Grid Layout, is a two-dimensional grid-based layout system with rows and columns, making it easier to design web pages without
having to use floats and positioning. Like tables, grid layout allow us to align elements into columns and rows.

FLEX
The CSS Flexbox offers a one-dimensional layout. It is helpful in allocating and aligning the space among items in a container.
It works with all kinds of display devices and screen sizes.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Rows and column for grid

The lines between columns are called column lines.
The lines between rows are called row lines.
The spaces between each column/row are called gaps.
grid-template-rows: It define the height of each row.
grid-template-column: It define the number of column.

